---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Jordan Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/jordan/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'UAE for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/uae' },
  { title: 'Egypt for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/egypt' },
  { title: 'Israel for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/israel' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'jordanFit', header: 'Jordan Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'JOD$355-507/mo', jordanFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'JOD$415-593/mo', jordanFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'JOD$320-457/mo', jordanFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'JOD$297-424/mo', jordanFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (Jordan Insurance)', entryAge: '60', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'JOD$50-150/mo', jordanFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'JOD$320-507', annual: 'JOD$3,840-6,084' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'JOD$439-677', annual: 'JOD$5,268-8,124' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'JOD$590-908', annual: 'JOD$7,080-10,896' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Visit', monthly: 'JOD$30-80/visit', annual: 'Affordable' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'JOD$150-400/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Jordan 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Jordan. Petra, Dead Sea, stable kingdom, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Jordan"
  subheadline="Jordan offers Petra wonders, Dead Sea healing, stable monarchy, moderate Islam, and medical tourism hub—a safe and culturally rich Middle Eastern destination for adventurous retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/jordan-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Jordan</h2>
  <p>
    Jordan offers Petra (New Wonder of World), Dead Sea's healing properties, stable Hashemite monarchy, moderate Islam, and regional medical tourism hub. For adventurous retirees seeking Middle Eastern culture with stability and good healthcare, Jordan provides safe and fascinating experience.
  </p>

  <p>
    Amman is the capital with best healthcare and expat community. Aqaba offers Red Sea resort living. Dead Sea has wellness focus. Petra area provides ancient wonder access. Most expats choose Amman for healthcare and services.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Regional medical tourism hub; good private</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Arabic; English widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> JOD$700-1,400/month (~$990-1,970 USD); moderate</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Mediterranean/desert; pleasant</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Stable; moderate; hospitable</li>
      <li><strong>Safety:</strong> One of Middle East's safest countries</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Jordan Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Jordan is regional medical tourism hub—King Hussein Cancer Center, Jordan Hospital, and private facilities provide excellent care. Many doctors trained in US/UK. Medical tourists come from Gulf states and Iraq. Most conditions treatable locally; complex cases may use Dubai.
  </p>

  <p>
    Private healthcare good and affordable. Medical tourism specialty. English widely spoken in healthcare. International insurance recommended for comprehensive coverage and regional mobility.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Medical Tourism Hub</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Jordan is established medical tourism destination. Excellent private hospitals at moderate prices. King Hussein Cancer Center is regional leader. Good specialists available. English-speaking doctors. Dubai provides backup for most complex cases.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Jordan has accessible visa options:
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Visa on arrival for most nationalities (30 days, extendable). Jordan Pass includes visa and sites.
  </p>

  <h3>Multiple Entry Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Available for frequent visitors. Good for regional exploration.
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For stays over 30 days. Various categories. Straightforward process.
  </p>

  <h3>Investment Residence</h3>
  <p>
    For those investing in Jordan. Real estate or business investment routes.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Jordan:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Residence:</strong> Health insurance recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Regional:</strong> Gulf/Middle East coverage helpful</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Jordan</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance recommended for comprehensive coverage. Local private care is good medical tourism hub. Dubai provides backup for complex cases. Good combination of local quality and regional access.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Jordan, Middle East network important:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Jordan</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Middle East network</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Dubai access:</strong> Regional backup for complex care</li>
    <li><strong>Local quality:</strong> Good medical tourism infrastructure</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for Jordan retirement.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Jordan (JOD ~1.41 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Amman base:</strong> Best healthcare access</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Local care affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Regional network:</strong> Use designated hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>Medical tourism:</strong> Good value procedures</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: History Enthusiast, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,500/month pension. Residence permit. Amman.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with Middle East coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~JOD$380/month (~$535). Petra access; regional backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Wellness Seeker, 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $3,000/month income. Long-term visa. Dead Sea area.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global comprehensive.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~JOD$480/month (~$675). Healing retreat; global coverage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: NGO Retiree, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,200/month pension. Residence permit. Amman.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with regional coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~JOD$330/month (~$465). Development community; affordable coverage.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Jordan safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very safe—one of Middle East's safest countries. Stable Hashemite monarchy. Tourism well-managed. Avoid Syrian border areas. Low crime. Royal family popular. Jordan has navigated regional conflicts well.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need Arabic?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Helpful but not essential—English widely spoken in Amman, tourism, healthcare. Arabic enriches experience. Many Jordanians educated abroad. Healthcare accessible in English. Learning basics appreciated.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What's the expat community like?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Established—NGO workers, diplomats, business expats. Amman has international schools, restaurants, social clubs. Large refugee support community. Welcoming to foreigners. Active social scene possible.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about Dead Sea?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Unique experience—lowest point on Earth, mineral-rich water, therapeutic mud. Luxury resorts along shore. Health tourism specialty. Day trips from Amman or stay at resorts. Genuine wellness benefits for skin, joints.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Jordan coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Jordan authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
